    "description": {
      "value": "\r\n<p class=\"source\"><b>Source</b> <a href=\"http://amzn.to/2z71S07\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">PZO1140</a></p>\r\n<p><b>Price</b> 25 gp</p>\r\n<p>The vivid and thorny dragon rose is admired for its hardiness but is difficult to cultivate.</p>\r\n<p><b>Gather</b> DC 18; <b>Yield</b> 1 dose</p>\r\n<p><b>Terrain</b> any forests or mountains</p>\r\n<p><b>Preparation</b> The petals of a dragon rose must be delicately removed from the stem and then soaked in a mixture brewed from the flower stalk's sap for 2 hours; this requires a successful DC 15 <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/craft\">Craft</a> (alchemy) check.</p>\r\n<p><b>Use</b> A dose of prepared dragon rose petals crushed in the hand and then smeared on a weapon (this is a <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Standard-Actions\">standard action</a>) infuses the weapon with a <a class=\"spell\" href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/magic/all-spells/m/magic-aura\">magic aura</a>. For 1 hour, the weapon can bypass <a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/rules-for-monsters/universal-monster-rules#TOC-Damage-Reduction-Ex-or-Su-\">DR</a>/magic, although it doesn't gain any bonus on attack or damage rolls.</p>\r\n",
